{
  "texts": [
    "The Kenyan writer and scholar Ngugi wa Thiong'o (1986), for example, has done extensive research on the cultural diversity embedded in Kenya's multilingual heritage.",
    "Language conveys the situatedness of knowledge.",
    "It influences how we see our world, which visions we follow, how we perceive colors, tastes, time.",
    "In Kiswahili, Arabic and Amharic, for example, time is measured not only from one hour to the next, but in relation to sunrise and sunset.",
    "Thus, 7 a.m. depends on the season because it is always the first hour after sunrise."
  ]
}